ission is to promote the construction management profession and the use of qualified construction managers on capital projects and programs.  CMAA@UIC works with CMAA Chicago to provide educational, networking, and professional opportunities to graduates of the construction management program at UIC. In addition to being a registered student organization at UIC, our chapter is recognized by CMAA National Headquarters and chartered in affiliation with CMAA Chicago.  Contact us: uic.cmaa@gmail.com       Leadership   Executive Board:   President: Francisco Lopez  Vice President: Jacob Miguest  Treasurer: Zaneta Marcinik   Faculty Advisor:   Hossein Ataei        Activities   Recent networking activities:   Career night and networking session with Clayco Inc.  Educational seminar on lean construction by Turner Construction Co.  Site visit to Willis Tower repositioning project  Site visit to Ozinga concrete production plant   Present goals:   Continue to increase student member enrollment  Connect members with construction management firms in Chicago  Increase the number of site visits in Chicagoland area  Organize more networking and professional events with CMAA Chicago           Undergraduate    Back to main content           Admitted Students    Admissions    Accreditation    Civil Engineering Major    Courses    Minors    Internships and Jobs    Student Groups    Student Profiles    Student Resources                   UIC Logo         College of  Engineering           Quicklinks    Graduate Resources    Undergraduate Resources    Room Reservation Form    ABET Accreditation         Contact   Department of Civil and Materials Engineering  2095 Engineering Research Facility, 842 W. Taylor St., Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-3428  Fax: (312) 996-2426  cme@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    LinkedIn    Twitter    Instagram             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information 